.TH DHCONSOLED 1 "July 2026" "DigiHub" "DigiHub User Manual"
.SH NAME
dhconsoled \- run ttyd for DigiHub's browser\-based web console
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dhconsoled
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dhconsoled
runs
.BR ttyd (1)
with a login shell
.RI ( "bash \-l" )
as its command, giving a full terminal in the browser. There is no
username or password prompt \-\- DigiHub already assumes a
trusted\-network, no\-auth model for every other
.BR dhweb (1)
page (see
.BR dhmode (1),
.BR dhrig (1),
etc.); the console follows the same one instead of being the one page
that asks. Don't expose DigiHub to the open internet \-\- see
.BR dhconsole (1)
for the full warning.
.PP
.B dhconsoled
is designed to run under systemd as the
.B dhconsole.service
unit, not to be started manually. Unlike
.BR dhgpsmonitor.service
or
.BR dhweb.service ,
it is
.B not
enabled automatically by
.BR install.sh ;
it stays off until
.BR dhconsole (1)
turns it on.
.PP
.B dhconsole.service
runs as the DigiHub operator account (its
.B User=
directive is templated at install time, the same as
.BR dhweb.service ),
not as root \-\- there is no PAM authentication step to need root for.
The interactive shell has exactly the privilege that account already
has, nothing more (e.g. its own sudo rights, if any).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Turn the console on (starts/enables this service automatically):
.B dhconsole on
.TP
Check the running service's status and recent log output:
.B systemctl status dhconsole
.br
.B journalctl \-u dhconsole \-f
.TP
Open the console once running:
.B http://<digihub\-host>:7681
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/systemd/system/dhconsole.service
The systemd unit that runs this daemon, installed and enabled by
.BR dhconsole (1)
on first use.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.B dhconsoled
does not exit under normal operation; it runs until stopped (e.g. by
systemd).
.TP
.B 1
The shared UI library could not be loaded, or
.B ttyd
is not installed.
.SH AUTHOR
Steve de Bode \- W0FFS
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR dhconsole (1),
